(3) A person shall not— (a) delay or obstruct an investigating officer, in the performance of the investigating officer’s functions; (b) refuse to give an investigating officer any reasonable assistance that the investigating officer may require for the purpose of exercising that investigating officer’s powers; or (c) give an investigating officer false or misleading information in answer to an inquiry made by the investigating officer.
